==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Revel
<hw>Rev"el</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF. <ets>revel</ets> rebellion,
disorder, feast, sport. See <er>Revel</er>, <pos>v. i.</pos>]</ety>
<def>A feast with loose and noisy jollity; riotous festivity or
merrymaking; a carousal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This day in mirth and <qex>revel</qex> to dispend.</q>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Some men ruin . . . their bodies by incessant
<qex>revels</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Rambler.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Master of the revels</b></col>, <col><b>Revel
master</b></col></mcol>. <cd>Same as <cref>Lord of misrule</cref>, under
<er>Lord</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Revel</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Revel
<hw>Rev"el</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Reveled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr> or <conjf>Revelled</conjf>; <pos>p.
pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Reveling</conjf> or
<conjf>Revelling</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OF. <ets>reveler</ets> to
revolt, rebel, make merry, fr. L. <ets>rebellare</ets>. See
<er>Rebel</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To feast in a riotous manner; to
carouse; to act the bacchanalian; to make merry.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To move playfully; to indulge without
restraint.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Where joy most <xex>revels</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Revel</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Revel
<hw>Re*vel"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>revellere</ets>; <ets>re-</ets> + <ets>vellere</ets> to pluck,
pull.]</ety> <def>To draw back; to retract.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Harvey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Revelate</ent>⟦br⟧
